[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Bank branch coverage in NI[bold]We were asked to provide clarity on our written submission of paragraph 28 which gives details on branch closures in the past two years. The following table shows the number of branches that are currently open, provided by the four largest banks in NI.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Bank of Ireland
[normal]35
[normal]Danske Bank
[normal]53
[normal]First Trust
[normal]32
[normal]Ulster Bank
[normal]79
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Building Societies in [bold]NI[bold]The main building societies with branch facilities in NI are Nationwide and the Progressive. Nationwide offer a range of curren
[normal]t account services. They have 14
[normal] main branche
[normal]s.
[normal] As mentioned at the committee on 11 September, there have been closures of agency services
[normal] provided by
[normal] Nationwide in the past. Nationwide previously had nine agencies (private insurance brokers and estate agents) operating in NI that carried a small float to service customers with current accounts. All of these agencies closed in 2008. Consumers must now visit one of the 14 branches for face to face service.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]January 2014
